natural problem: Find the largest value of $c$ such that $\frac{c^2 + 6c -27}{c-3} +2c = 23$.
natural solution: Factoring the quadratic gives $\frac{(c-3)(c+9)}{c-3} +2c= 23$. Canceling the common factor gives $c+9 + 2c = 23$.

theorem
fixes c :: real
assumes h0 : "(c powr 2 + 6 * c - 27) / (c - 3) + 2 * c = 23"
shows  "c = 14 / 3"

 Solving this equation gives $c = \boxed{\frac{14}{3}}$.
 *)

fixes c :: real
